data.value:
The symbol of peace on the continent of Europe is Strazburg, the capital of the Alsace region located in the north-east of the country. The city has been a UNESCO World Heritage Site since 1988. Located between France and France, the city has a multicultural structure as it is located on the German border. It is the capital of Europe because it hosts the European Parliament.
Grande Ile, the historic center of the city, offers the best examples of French and German architecture. The 300-year-old and still running astrological clock, and the glorious gothic cathedral with its intricately carved exterior is enough to make Strazburgone of France's sights. Discover La Petite France, the gastronomy of the Alsace region, and cross the European Bridge to Germany. Pegasus and Turkish Airlines fly directly to Strazburg.
